Business Brief -- Toyota Motor Corp.:
   Firm to Invest $90 Million
   To Expand Kentucky Plant
The addition also includes expanding the plant's capacity
to build front-axle and rear-axle sets to 420,000 annually,
from 240,000 currently. Toyota officials said they expect the
addition to be completed in the spring of 1994, and add 200
new jobs and 200,000 square feet to the powertrain plant.